|WKBDESCRIPTION
===========

|YKOParasites are finite living infections that improve hit point recovery,
spell point recovery, or both while carrying real costs. Carriers --
larvae, worms, cysts, and stranger things -- are sold at |YKBThe Brood
Apothecary|YKO in DarkWind City, south of Xenor Road. Inside the shop,
|YKBlist parasites|YKO and |YKBdescribe parasite <name>|YKO preview
each strain before you commit.

Once swallowed, the infection is represented as active internal equipment.
Its burden and any sigils therefore use the same stat and sigil machinery as
worn gear, while remaining separate from cyberware location conflicts.

Infection is voluntary: buy a carrier, hold it, and |YKBswallow|YKO or
|YKBeat|YKO it. Each strain has a minimum level, some accept only hosts
of a particular guild, and only one parasite can live in you at a time.

While you are hurt or drained, the parasite mends you each pulse: some
strains restore hit points, some restore spell points, and the
strongest do both. It never heals past your maximums. In exchange it
exacts a burden that varies by strain: reduced maximum hit or spell
points, weakened dodge, damage, or swings, and sometimes an appetite
that drinks your spell points while it works. If you cannot feed a
hungry parasite's full appetite, it goes starved and does not mend you
that pulse.

A parasite lives for a fixed amount of online time; its clock pauses
while you are logged out, and it goes still for good when the time runs
out. It dies with you if you die, and guild-bound strains die if you
leave their guild. Use |YKBparasite|YKO to inspect your infection:
healing, burden, appetite, fed or starved state, and time remaining.

To be rid of one early, return to The Brood Apothecary and use
|YKBpurge parasite|YKO for a 2500 gold fee.|XX0

